HEADWORD: Bilirubin
<hw>Bil`i*ru"bin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bilis</ets> biel + <ets>ruber</ets> red.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A reddish yellow pigment present in human
bile, and in that from carnivorous and herbivorous animals; the normal
biliary pigment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biliteral</ent>⟦br⟧
